Most of the cabin numbers are missing. However, cabin numbers can provide us an idea about the passenger location in the ship which can help in decide whether they survived. We'll extract the cabin letters and divide them into different categories. Missing values are added to a other class.

3.9 Age - Age in years¶

In [45]:
pd.isna(df.Age).sum()
Out[45]:
263

Quite a few missing values. We can fill them with median ages but not a good idea to take median of whole dataset. We can use the passenger names to infer if they are children, adult or older people. For example, if a name contains Master or Miss, they are likely to be younger in age. Similarly, if the name contains Mr, Mrs, or Dr., they are likely older in age.

In [46]:
df.Name.head()  # Second word, immediately after a comma, seems to be the title

3         Futrelle, Mrs. Jacques Heath (Lily May Peel)
4                             Allen, Mr. William Henry
Name: Name, dtype: object

In [60]:
train = processed_df[processed_df.dataset == "train"].copy()
y = train.Survived.values
del train["Survived"], train["dataset"]

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(train, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=5)

X_valid = processed_df[processed_df.dataset == "valid"].copy()
del X_valid["Survived"], X_valid["dataset"]

print(X_train.shape, X_test.shape, X_valid.shape)

Check for any unusual correlation between the features.

Build a RandomForest, SVM and XGBoost classifier models.

print(f"Training accuracy: {round(accuracy_score(y_train, train_pred)*100, 1)}%")

train_pred = xgb.predict(X_train)
test_pred = xgb.predict(X_test)

print(f"Training accuracy: {round(accuracy_score(y_train, train_pred)*100, 1)}%")
print(f"Testing accuracy : {round(accuracy_score(y_test, test_pred)*100, 1)}%")

print()
print(classification_report(y_test, test_pred))

Above results are obtained after a trying lots of combination of hyperparameters. SVM and XGBoost sometimes gave a slightly higher accuracy than RandomForest but both these models also tended to overfit. RandomForest found a balance between train and test accuracy for above combination. We'll take the RandomForest as the final model. Only thing that's left now is making prediction on the holdout dataset.
